#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Configuring Multiple Branch Servers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:36
msgid ""
"Create a YAML file describing the infrastructure you intend to install.  For "
"an example YAML file, see xref:retail-mass-config-yaml.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:37
msgid ""
"On a clean {susemgr} installation, import the YAML file you have created:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:40
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_yaml --from-yaml filename.yaml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:43
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:87
msgid "See the [command]``retail_yaml --help`` output for additional options."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:44
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:88
msgid ""
"In the {susemgr} {webui}, check that your systems are listed and displaying "
"correctly, and the formulas you require are available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:46
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:90
msgid ""
"Create activation keys for each of your branch servers, connect them using "
"bootstrap, and configure them as proxy servers.  For more information, see "
"xref:retail:retail-install-unified.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:47
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:91
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``States`` tab, click btn:[Apply Highstate] to deploy your "
"configuration changes for each branch server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:50
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:94
msgid ""
"If you need to change your configuration, you can edit the YAML file at any "
"time, and use the [command]``retail_yaml --from-yaml`` command to upload the "
"new configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:54
msgid ""
"Use empty profiles together with activation keys to onboard all the systems "
"of your infrastructure.  Use an activation key to assign the channels listed "
"in xref:retail:retail-install-setup.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "Terminal Mass Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:61
msgid ""
"If you are working in an environment with many terminals, you might find it "
"easier to configure the terminals automatically with a pre-defined "
"configuration file, rather than configuring each terminal individually."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:64
msgid ""
"You will need to have your infrastructure planned out ahead of time, "
"including the IP addresses, hostnames, and domain names of branch servers "
"and terminals.  You will also require the hardware (MAC) addresses of each "
"terminal."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:71
msgid ""
"The settings specified in the configuration file cannot always be "
"successfully applied.  In cases where there is a conflict, {productname} "
"will ignore the request in the file.  This is especially important when "
"designating hostnames.  You should always check that the details have been "
"applied as expected after using this configuration method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure Multiple Terminals"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Configuring Multiple Terminals"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:80
msgid ""
"Create a YAML file describing the infrastructure you intend to install, "
"specifying the hardware address for each terminal.  For an example YAML "
"file, see xref:retail-mass-config-yaml.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:81
msgid ""
"On a clean {productname} installation, import the YAML file you have created:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:92
msgid "Connect your terminals according to your infrastructure plan."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "Export Configuration to Mass Configuration File"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:99
msgid ""
"If you already have a configuration that you would like to export to a YAML "
"file, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_yaml --to-yaml filename.yaml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:104
msgid ""
"This can be a good way to create a basic mass configuration file.  However, "
"it is important to check the file before using it, because some mandatory "
"configuration entries may be missing."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-mass-config.adoc:109
msgid ""
"When you are designing your configuration and creating the YAML file, ensure "
"the branch server ID matches the fully qualified hostname, and the Salt ID.  "
"If these do not match, the bootstrap script could fail."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migrate {slepos} 11 to {smr}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:7
msgid ""
"This section describes migrating from an existing {slepos} 11 installation "
"to a new {susemgr} installation.  You can perform this migration all at once "
"by creating a data dump in a single file, and then moving it to the new "
"server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:10
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can perform the migration in stages by creating a data "
"dump for each branch, and moving them to the new server one by one.  "
"Importing and deploying the converted data can also be done in one or "
"multiple steps, depending on your environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migration with Complete Data Dump"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:17
msgid ""
"In this procedure, you create a single data dump in an XML file, convert it "
"to YAML, and migrate it to the new infrastructure all at once."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:20
msgid ""
"Install a {smr} server {productnumber}.  For more information, see xref:"
"retail:retail-install-unified.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:22
msgid ""
"On the SLEPOS Admin server export all the data stored in LDAP to an XML "
"file.  Run this command as an administrator:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:25
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "posAdmin --export --type xml --file dumpfile.xml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:28
msgid ""
"The resulting [literal]``dumpfile.xml`` file will contain global "
"information, with parts about images, hardware and its partitioning, and the "
"description of the branch servers with networking data, services, and "
"attached terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:30
msgid ""
"Move the XML file to the newly created {susemgr} server, and convert it to "
"YAML:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_migration dumpfile.xml retail.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:39
msgid ""
"Review the generated YAML file ([literal]``retail.yml``) and adjust it as "
"necessary.  Consider ``HWTYPE`` group naming and image name and version "
"changes in the partitioning data.  Group names must not exceed the "
"56 character limit.  You can shorten the names as needed, and the image "
"names must match the images in {susemgr}.  The [option]``--save-mapping`` "
"option can help you with this task."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:43
msgid ""
"Also check whether there are duplicate MAC addresses of the terminals in the "
"generated YAML file.  Choose which entry you want to keep.  If there are "
"duplicate MAC addresses, importing the YAML file will fail."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:48
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:106
msgid ""
"{slepos} images will not be migrated. You must rebuild the images using the "
"OS image building functionality.  For more information about building "
"images, see xref:administration:image-management.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:51
msgid "Import the complete data (YAML) with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_yaml --from-yaml retail.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:57
msgid ""
"You can see statistical data while importing.  Then check the results in the "
"{webui}. In menu:Main Menu[Systems > Systems > All], find empty profiles, "
"and in menu:Main Menu[Systems > Groups], the groups for the hardware "
"configuration, the branches, servers, and terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:63
msgid ""
"To finalize the branch server migration, you must install the branch server "
"machines as Salt clients and bootstrap them as proxies.  For more "
"information about proxy installation, see xref:retail:retail-install."
"adoc[].  For more information about using an activation key to assign the "
"required channels, see xref:retail:retail-install-setup.adoc[].  After "
"onboarded to {susemgr}, the branch servers machines are connected with the "
"empty profiles (by FQDN), and so they will get the Retail configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:65
msgid ""
"After all the branches are migrated, shutdown and remove the old SLEPOS "
"Admin Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:69
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migration with Branch by Branch Data Dump"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:72
msgid ""
"In this procedure, you migrate the SLEPOS infrastructure and the branches "
"one by one, first exporting and then importing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:75
msgid ""
"Install a {smr} server {productnumber} For more information, see xref:retail:"
"retail-install-unified.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:77
msgid "On every branch server:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:83
msgid ""
"These dumps will contain only the LDAP data of the branch, and any global "
"data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:85
msgid ""
"Similarily, you can export the LDAP data of every branch if you run the "
"command on the Admin server with the branch credentials explicitly specified:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:89
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"posAdmin --export --type xml --file dumpfile.xml --user $branch_dn \\\n"
"    --password $password\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:92
msgid ""
"For background information about SLEPOS branch server configuration, see "
"https://documentation.suse.com/sle-pos/11-SP3/html/SLEPOS-guide/cha."
"slepos_branchserv.html."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:97
msgid ""
"Review the generated YAML file ([literal]``retail.yml``) and adjust it as "
"necessary.  Consider ``HWTYPE`` group naming and image name and version "
"changes in the partitioning data.  You can shorten the names as needed, and "
"the image names must match the images in {susemgr}.  The [option]``--save-"
"mapping`` option can help you with this task."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:101
msgid ""
"Check whether there are duplicate MAC addresses of the terminals in the "
"generated YAML file.  Choose which entry you want to keep.  As long as there "
"are duplicate MAC addresses, {susemgr} will refuse importing the YAML file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:110
msgid ""
"The data can be imported branch by branch.  For each branch perform the "
"following steps:"
msgstr ""

#.  . Replace each old SLEPOS branch server with a {smr} branch server (see https://www.suse.com/documentation/suse-manager-for-retail-3-2/retail-getting-started/retail.chap.install.html[Install Branch Server]) and connect it to the {smr} server (the same procedure as for https://www.suse.com/documentation/suse-manager-for-retail-3-2/retail-getting-started/retail.chap.admin.html#retail.sect.admin.branch_mass_config[Branch Server Mass Configuration]).
#.  +
#.  Use the empty profiles together with activation keys to onboard all the systems of your infrastructure.
#.  Use an activation key to assign the channels listed in https://www.suse.com/documentation/suse-manager-for-retail-3-2/retail-getting-started/retail.chap.install.html[Configuring Server].
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:117
msgid "Run the import command for one branch after the other:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_yaml --from-yaml retail.yml --branch <branch_name>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:123
msgid "Repeat the command for every branch."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:128
msgid ""
"To finalize each branch server migration, you must install the branch server "
"machine as a Salt-based client and bootstrap it as a proxy.  For more "
"information about proxy installation, see xref:retail-install.adoc#retail."
"sect.install.branch[Installing and Registering].  For more information about "
"using an activation key to assign the required channels, see xref:retail-"
"install.adoc#retail.sect.install.install.config[Configuring Server].  After "
"onboarded to {smr}, the branch server machine is connected with the empty "
"profile (by FQDN), and so it will get the Retail configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:130
msgid ""
"Apply Highstate on the branch server; this will happen automatically if "
"[guimenu]``Configuration File Deployment`` is enabled."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:132
msgid "Boot the terminals of the branch."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:134
msgid ""
"After all the branches are migrated, shut down and remove the old SLEPOS "
"Admin Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "Converting XML to YAML"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:142
msgid ""
"When you perform a migration using one of the methods in this chapter, one "
"of the steps takes the XML data dump file from {slepos}, and converts it to "
"a YAML file for {smr}.  The tool that performs this conversion has "
"additional features, which are outlined in this section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:144
msgid "To validate the XML file before conversion, and print any errors:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:147
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_migration dumpfile.xml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:151
msgid "To write a mapping file called [path]``map.yml``:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:154
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_migration dumpfile.xml  --save-mapping map.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:157
msgid "The mapping file contains two dictionaries:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:158
msgid ""
"[systemitem]``images``, which maps old {slepos} images to new images built "
"in {susemgr}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:160
msgid ""
"[systemitem]``groups``, which maps legacy {slepos} "
"[systemitem]``scCashRegister`` objects to {susemgr} [systemitem]``HWTYPE`` "
"groups.  Group names must not exceed the 56 character limit."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:162
msgid "The mapping file should be edited as required for your environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:165
msgid "To perform a conversion using a mapping file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:168
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_migration dumpfile.xml  retail.yml --mapping map.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:173
msgid ""
"If you are performing a branch-by-branch migration, the resulting "
"[path]``retail.yml`` file will contain a new version of {slepos} LDAP data.  "
"If you want to preserve any global changes in your {smr} settings, remove "
"the [systemitem]``global`` hardware types from the resulting [path]``retail."
"yml`` file before importing it.  Alternatively, you can import "
"[path]``retail.yml`` using this command to import only the new systems and "
"groups defined in the file, and leave any existing configuration settings "
"untouched:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:176
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_yaml --only-new\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Network Architecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:5
msgid "{smr} uses a layered architecture:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:7
msgid "The first layer contains the {susemgr} Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:9
msgid ""
"The second layer contains one or more branch servers to provide local "
"network and boot services.  It also contains one or more build hosts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:10
msgid ""
"The final layer contains any number of deployed point-of-service terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_arch.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Branch servers should be physically located close to point-of-service "
"terminals, such as in an individual store or branch office.  We recommend "
"you have a fast network connection between the branch server and its "
"terminals.  Branch servers provide services for PXE boot, and act as an "
"image cache, Salt broker, and proxy for software components (RPM packages).  "
"The branch server can also manage local networking, and provide DHCP and DNS "
"services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:21
msgid ""
"{smr} Branch servers are implemented as enhanced {susemgr} Proxy servers.  "
"For technical background information on {smr} Branch servers, see also the "
"documentation on {susemgr} Proxy servers (xref:installation:install-proxy-"
"unified.adoc[])."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Branch Server Network Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:28
msgid ""
"The branch server can operate in several different network configurations.  "
"The two most common configurations are a dedicated network, or a shared "
"network."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "Dedicated Network Architecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:35
msgid ""
"The branch server has a dedicated network interface card and terminals use "
"an isolated internal branch network.  In this configuration, the branch "
"server manages the internal network and provides DHCP, DNS, PXE, FTP, and "
"TFTP services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_dedicated_nic.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Shared Network Architecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:44
msgid ""
"The branch server and the terminals are connected to the same network as the "
"{susemgr} server.  In this configuration, the branch server is not required "
"to manage a network (DHCP and DNS services), but acts as a PXE boot server "
"and provides FTP and TFTP services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_shared_network.png"
msgstr ""

