#. type: Title =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Offline Use"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:7
msgid ""
"If the {productname} Server is offline, you can still perform some "
"operations on the terminals.  This is useful if the connection between the "
"branch server and the {productname} Server is unstable or has low "
"bandwidth.  This feature uses caching to perform updates."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Offline features and features relying on caching are available only for "
"{productname} Server 4.0 and above."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Offline Terminal Reboot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:18
msgid ""
"If the {productname} Server is offline, and a terminal is rebooted, it will "
"fall back to a previously installed image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:20
msgid "This will occur in these situations:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:22
msgid ""
"If the Saltboot formula has not started within a specified time (default "
"value is 60 seconds)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:23
msgid ""
"If the terminal does not acknowledge that the Saltboot formula has started."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:24
msgid ""
"If the root partition is specified on the kernel command line (handled by "
"the PXE formula), is mountable (and is not encrypted), and contains [path]``/"
"etc/ImageVersion`` (which is created by Kiwi)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:27
msgid ""
"You can adjust the timeout value by changing the [parameter]``SALT_TIMEOUT`` "
"kernel parameter.  The parameter is measured in seconds, and defaults to "
"[systemitem]``60``."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "SALT_TIMEOUT = 60\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:33
msgid "For more about kernel parameters, see xref:salt:formula-pxe.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cached Terminal Updates"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:39
msgid ""
"If there is low bandwidth between the branch server and the terminal, or for "
"optimization of terminal update process, POS images can be cached in advance "
"on the terminal and the upgrade performed on the terminals later on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:44
msgid ""
"This functionality requires the terminal to have a dedicated service "
"partition. A service partition is a partition mounted as `/srv/saltboot`.  "
"This partition must be created before the system partition and large enough "
"to store a POS image.  To ensure that terminals will always have such a "
"partition, use the Saltboot formula for terminal hardware type to specify "
"the partition details.  For more information, see xref:salt:formula-saltboot."
"adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:46
msgid ""
"When the service partition is set up on the terminal, a POS image can be "
"downloaded in advance by applying the `saltboot.cache_image` state:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt $TERMINALID state.apply saltboot.cache_image\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:52
msgid ""
"This can be done regularly to ensure that terminals always have an uptodate "
"POS image downloaded."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-offline.adoc:53
msgid ""
"When the terminal is rebooted and an uptodate POS image is found in the "
"service partition, the terminal will automatically use this cached image for "
"system redeployment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Before You Migrate"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:5
msgid ""
"This document is intended to guide you through migration your {slepos} or "
"older {smr} installation (3.1 or 3.2) to the newest version of {smr}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:8
msgid ""
"This document is divided into scenarios.  Pick the scenario that best suits "
"your environment, and follow the instructions in that section to migrate "
"your installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:12
msgid ""
"Ensure your existing installation is fully updated, and that you have "
"performed a backup, before you begin your migration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prepare to Migrate from {slepos}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:21
msgid ""
"{slepos} cannot be upgraded directly to {smr}, so the migration process "
"requires you to perform some manual configuration.  To assist you in the "
"migration, as much information as possible about the existing hardware "
"configuration and network infrastructure is recorded.  Then this information "
"is used for rebuilding the new {smr} installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:25
msgid ""
"In some cases, this will require a lengthy downtime to perform the "
"migration.  If you are not able to manage downtime, you can install new "
"servers and run them in parallel to the existing ones while you perform the "
"migration.  This is especially relevant for large installations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:29
msgid ""
"It is possible to run a SLEPOS Admin server and a {susemgr} server in "
"parallel.  In such a scenario, branches that have been migrated will run on "
"the {susemgr} server, while those that have not yet been migrated can "
"continue to run on the SLEPOS Admin server.  This includes all operations, "
"such as adding new terminals, or building and deploying new images."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:33
msgid ""
"However, if you run network services (especially DHCP) on the branch "
"servers, you will not be able to run both old and new branch servers in "
"parallel on the same branch, because they can conflict with each other.  "
"This can result in multiple terminals having the same IP address, or "
"terminals randomly assigned to different branch servers.  If you need to "
"migrate in this environment, and you want to configure a new branch server "
"while the branch is still running on old infrastructure, make sure that the "
"new branch server is not connected to the network with the terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-prepare-migration.adoc:34
msgid ""
"If your branch server does not provide DHCP services, you can configure the "
"new one in parallel and, when you are ready, change the configuration of "
"your DHCP server from the old to the new branch server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-saltboot-diagram.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Saltboot Diagram"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-saltboot-diagram.adoc:5
msgid ""
"The saltboot process involves the {productname} Server, a terminal running "
"the saltboot ``initrd``, and the branch server providing the saltboot "
"services to the terminal."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-saltboot-diagram.adoc:7
msgid ""
"This sequence diagram explains how the three components interact with each "
"other to boot a {smr} terminal."
msgstr ""

